We’re back! I didn’t realize how much I missed doing this! 

I had a very warm welcome back on last Friday afternoon haha! Even though I ate it pretty bad I’m happy that I went out there, put myself in the right spot and went for it.

My board hit me in the ribs and across my chest when I was getting worked but I pushed through the pain and went back out the next day for some redemption. I knew I had to take advantage of the glassy conditions we had and shake off the wipeout from the day before. I was really happy to have made a wave (even if it was a small one) 

There’s definitely been some hurdles to overcome leading into this season but after this opening swell I’m feeling good and I’m so excited to be back out there! 

@roxy @sos_shapes @redbullusa @redbull @redbullsurfing  #redbullmagnitude
@roxy 🪸

If I hear “and with that the 2022 season comes to an end” one more time. 

For me 2022 was a crazy year. I really didn’t know what to expect. I had just come off my injury in January, I didn’t have a set schedule of contests and I just felt like I was floating around a little bit. That opened the door for so many amazing opportunities that I always dreamed of. I don’t think I’ve ever traveled as much as I did this year. I met so many cool new people, went to some new places and definitely got out of my comfort zone. This was a year of growth for me all around. From a young age I have always put so much pressure on myself and through the years it has worn on me to the point where sometimes I just want to quit. I had to go to those painful and uncomfortable places to give myself the chance to be free and live in the moment. I just want to say thank you so much to my sponsors @redbull @roxy @dryrobe @rumaner.surfboards for all the fun times and opportunities this year! I also really want to thank @seanpurps805 @katiemabes @stanfiess @mikypicon @mathiasmaallem @christinereppa @amyschultz_pt @marcomilanophysio @deep2peak @tuturisse for being in my corner this year and continuously supporting me 🙏🏼
L8r 👋🏼

When I was little, my brother @giorgiogomez and I used to play the Kelly Slater Pro Surfer game on play station. My favorite spot to surf in the game was Cortes Bank. I was obsessed with it and so enamored by this spot that just seemed like a myth. 

Never in my life did I think I would be able to surf here. It makes me emotional to look back on my younger self and be able to say you did it.

This would not have been possible without @chuckpatterson @bradrambo @brandon_rambo @mv_legend90 
I can’t thank you guys enough. I will never forget this day 🤩

Thank you @chuckpatterson for not only towing me into these waves but just always being there for me through the years and giving me the push to get back up when I feel defeated. I’m forever grateful! 

I’m so happy I finally got to ride my beautiful tow board shaped by @sos_shapes , thank you Sean! It worked so good! 

Thank you god for this life! I hope I get to come back here someday! 🙏🏼

Happy to be here in Panama for the @panamericansurf Games! This competition is a stepping stone to Olympic qualification. The top 8 countries from this event will receive a spot in the @santiago2023oficial Pan American Games in Chile, later this year where the Olympic spot will be decided. I was so excited to surf my round 1 heat the other day! The waves were firing! I’m first heat of the women’s round tomorrow morning at 8:20 am 💚💪🏼🙏🏼 Thank you to my team and @colombiasurfing for all the support! Photos @nat.wild.photos

Semi final finish for me here in Panama! My goal going into this event was to qualify for the @santiago2023oficial Pan American Games and I’m really happy to have accomplished that and give myself the chance to fight for Olympic qualification later this year in Chile. Thank you to everyone in my corner and @panamericansurf for a great event 🙏🏼💜

Happiest of birthdays to my mom @brandibr80 💖 I’m so blessed to have you as my mom. As I get older I realize more and more what goes into being a mother and I’m forever grateful for everything you’ve done and continue to do for me. All those weekends driving me and @giorgiogomez to surf contests, all the hours spent on the beach filming us from sun up to sun down, all the hand made Halloween costumes, helping us with our homework, traveling with us around the world for competitions and too many other things that would be too much to write. You take a lot for granted as a kid and when I look back on all those amazing memories I’ve made with my mom I can’t help but smile. Love you @brandibr80 ⭐️

Thank you Chile! Stoked to win the gold here in sup surfing in some tough conditions. It was an honor to share the podium with my good friends @alineadisaka and @vaniato, congratulations on your medals! Pichilemu has been somewhere I’ve always wanted to visit and I had the best time here. Thank you to the locals for sharing your line up with us and all the people of Pichilemu for welcoming us 🙏🏼 

I qualified for this Pan Ams in two divisions, Shortboard and Sup surfing. For those that don’t know, I won gold in sup surfing four years ago in Peru where the last Pan Ams was held. I’m very happy to have gone back to back. I was really focusing on getting a good result in shortboard but unfortunately it was the opposite for me. It was heartbreaking to lose so early because I had put so much effort in the last few month’s preparing for this event. At the end of the day everything is a learning experience and only you have the power to decide how you respond to adversity. 

Some people know my background while others only know me solely as a big wave surfer. I’ve surfed my whole life and competed in surfing when I was young, started sup surfing when I was 13, and then I eventually transitioned into big wave surfing. My path has definitely been different to say the least and I’m still learning to embrace it and stay true to myself. Sup surfing opened many doors for me and has led me to where I am now and I will be forever grateful for that part of my career. 

Thank you to my team and everyone who has been in my corner especially the past year. Love you guys and your support means more to me than you will ever know 🙏🏼 

Thank you @santiago2023oficial for a great event and @olimpicocol @colombiasurfing and the country of Colombia for giving me the opportunity to represent you ❤️🇨🇴

These videos are from my first two days back at Jaws last year after being out of the water with an injury the whole season before.

The first video was my very first wave back, I wanted to put myself in a good spot to get a wave quickly and get it out of the way. My board ended up hitting me in the ribs underwater and I thought for sure my run was over right then and there. This was definitely the worst wipeout I’ve had so far.

The second video was the very next day and I was hurting. It’s rare to get those fun glassy days at jaws and I was so upset that I wasn’t feeling 100% to be able to perform. I could barely lay on my board or paddle and I thought for sure I wasn’t going to surf. I ended up paddling out and sat in the lineup all day and tried to push through. I was getting ready to quit and go in when this set came through and @paigealms screamed at me to paddle. 

To come back the next day, overcome the fall and be able to successfully ride a wave meant so much to me. It had been such a long road to feel ready to surf jaws again. This was a big milestone and learning experience for me. I had such an amazing crew of people who helped me achieve my goals last year and I’m excited for this season! 🫶🏼
